            <item>
                <title>Installing DynamixelWizard2 on Ubuntu</title>
                <description>&lt;p&gt;This is how you can install DynamixelWizard2 on Ubuntu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;!--more--&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Download &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;DynamixelWizard2Setup_x64&lt;/code&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;http://emanual.robotis.com/docs/en/software/dynamixel/dynamixel_wizard2/#software-installation&quot;&gt;ROBOTIS website&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Make the setup file executable &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;sudo chmod u+x DynamixelWizard2Setup_x64&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Run &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;./DynamixelWizard2Setup_x64&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Follow the installation step&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you get the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;DynamixelWizard2: symbol lookup error: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libGLX_mesa.so.0: undefined symbol: xcb_dri3_get_supported_modifiers
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Remove the file &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;libxcb-dri3.so.0&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;~/ROBOTIS/DynamixelWizard2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can now use DynamixelWizard2.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <pubDate>Sun, 08 Sep 2019 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
                <link>http://localhost:4000/2019/09/08/installing-dynamixelwizard2/</link>
